a little overwhelming.

257
00:17:08,174 --> 00:17:10,074
I'm so sorry.

258
00:17:10,976 --> 00:17:12,671
I didn't mean to overwhelm you.

259
00:17:12,945 --> 00:17:15,743
It's just that
when those gates open...

260
00:17:16,649 --> 00:17:19,880
...it's hard to close them.

261
00:17:22,588 --> 00:17:24,886
But they are closed now. Believe me.

262
00:17:25,157 --> 00:17:28,854
I'm so glad. I'm so glad you shared.

263
00:17:29,362 --> 00:17:31,990
And I'm glad that you're done.

264
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:36,797
So what do you say we....

265
00:17:39,038 --> 00:17:40,266
I'd like that.

266
00:17:52,084 --> 00:17:55,576
That was so good!

267
00:18:04,897 --> 00:18:06,364
Oh, oh.

268
00:18:09,568 --> 00:18:13,868
I can't believe you talked me into
this gumball-machine-Iooking ring.

269
00:18:14,273 --> 00:18:17,868
It's not a gumball-machine-Iooking ring.
It's a beautiful ring!

270
00:18:18,077 --> 00:18:19,567
No, it's not.

271
00:18:19,812 --> 00:18:23,407
When I looked at the other ring,
I could see Monica's face...

272
00:18:23,616 --> 00:18:27,450
...and I could see her saying yes.
Looking at this, I only see a ring.

273
00:18:27,653 --> 00:18:32,056
Unless I look at it really closely,
and then I can see my own eye.

274
00:18:36,829 --> 00:18:41,823
This is the most important thing I'll
ever do. I want to make it perfect.

275
00:18:42,935 --> 00:18:45,631
Maybe we could get
the other ring back.

276
00:18:45,871 --> 00:18:48,601
I heard where
the guy was gonna propose.

277
00:18:48,841 --> 00:18:52,607
-Maybe we could get him to trade rings.
-I can't do that.

278
00:18:52,812 --> 00:18:56,304
You certainly can't give her
that stupid gumball ring.

279
00:18:56,515 --> 00:19:00,508
-All right. Where was he going?
-Yeah, it's a restaurant....

280
00:19:00,886 --> 00:19:02,911
-The Rainbow something.
-Rainbow Room?

281
00:19:03,489 --> 00:19:04,478
Rainbow Grill?

282
00:19:04,657 --> 00:19:06,648
Somewhere Over the...?

283
00:19:08,093 --> 00:19:09,754
-L'Espace.
-Rainbow L'Espace!

284
00:19:09,929 --> 00:19:11,920
No, just L'Espace.

285
00:19:13,599 --> 00:19:16,898
I'd love to know how you got
from rainbow to L'Espace.

286
00:19:17,069 --> 00:19:18,798
No, you wouldn't.

287
00:19:19,638 --> 00:19:22,163
You don't wanna get in here.

288
00:19:30,149 --> 00:19:31,548
There he is.

289
00:19:31,717 --> 00:19:34,515
He hasn't proposed yet.
She has no ring on.

290
00:19:34,787 --> 00:19:38,655
Wow, you're good!
After this, we should solve crimes.

291
00:19:39,024 --> 00:19:40,150
Okay. Go get him.

292
00:19:40,826 --> 00:19:41,918
Oh, okay.

293
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:48,564
Excuse me. Could you
come with me? You have a phone call.

294
00:19:49,335 --> 00:19:51,303
-Who is it?
-It's your office.

295
00:19:51,637 --> 00:19:53,935
-Do you know who at my office?
-John.

296
00:19:54,106 --> 00:19:55,164
Oh, John! Great!

297
00:19:58,944 --> 00:20:00,809
-There he is.
-Hi. Okay.

298
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:03,014
There was a mix-up at the store.

299
00:20:03,282 --> 00:20:06,581
The ring you have was supposed
to be held for me.

300
00:20:06,819 --> 00:20:08,980
I'm gonna need to have that back.

301
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:15,757
In exchange, I'm willing to trade you
this beautiful, more expensive ring.

302
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:19,793
Wow, I would trade.

303
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:24,803
It is beautiful, but I'm gonna use
this one. Excuse me.

304
00:20:25,070 --> 00:20:28,437
This is my fiancée,
and her heart was set on that ring.

305
00:20:28,674 --> 00:20:30,369
Do you want to break her heart?

306
00:20:30,876 --> 00:20:34,073
Yeah. Do you want to break
a dying woman's heart?

307
00:20:35,014 --> 00:20:36,447
You're dying?

308
00:20:39,985 --> 00:20:41,543
Yeah, she's dying...

309
00:20:41,820 --> 00:20:43,981
...of a cough, apparently.

310
00:20:45,858 --> 00:20:49,988
It's my dying wish to have that ring.
If I'm not buried with it...

311
00:20:50,229 --> 00:20:53,323
...my spirit will wander
the netherworld--

312
00:20:53,566 --> 00:20:54,692
That's enough!

313
00:20:56,402 --> 00:20:58,097
Oh, I don't know.

314
00:21:00,139 --> 00:21:02,869
-Let me see it.
-Great. Okay, here.

315
00:21:05,311 --> 00:21:07,939
-All right, I'll do it.
-Thank you.

316
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:11,343
And you are about to marry
a wonderful man.

317
00:21:17,389 --> 00:21:19,550
Hey, I'm marrying a dead woman!

318
00:21:26,398 --> 00:21:27,387
Guys?

319
00:21:31,003 --> 00:21:33,870
I've got something important
to tell you.

320
00:21:34,607 --> 00:21:35,869
Guys?

321
00:21:37,409 --> 00:21:38,569
Guys?

322
00:21:38,811 --> 00:21:40,244
Guys?

323
